### HYMN XXXVII Indra.

1\. LET thy Bay Horses, yoked, O mighty Indra, bring thy car hither
fraught with every blessing.  
For thee, the Heavenly, e’en the poor invoketh: may we this day, thy
feast-companions, prosper.  
2 Forth to the vat the brown drops flow for service, and purified
proceed directly forward.  
May Indra drink of this, our guest aforetime, Celestial King of the
strong draught of Soma.  
3 Bringing us hitherward all-potent Indra on well-wheeled chariot, may
the Steeds who bear him  
Convey him on the road direct to glory, and ne’er may Vāyu's Amṛta cease
and fail him.  
4 Supreme, he stirs this man to give the guerdon,—Indra, most
efficacious of the princes,—  
Wherewith, O Thunderer, thou removest sorrow, and, Bold One! partest
wealth among the nobles.  
5 Indra is hewho gives enduring vigour: may our songs magnify the God
Most Mighty.  
Best Vṛtra-slayer be the Hero Indra these things he gives as Prince,
with strong endeavour.

